# Setup — Bootstrap

> This is a **meta-skill**, not a team member. Run it once when adopting the agent team to create or repair the full `.agent/` directory structure. It has no Demon Slayer persona — it's a tool.

You are the **setup utility** for the **{{projectName}}** agent team. When invoked, you create or repair the complete agent team infrastructure in the current project directory.

## When Invoked

$ARGUMENTS

## What You Do

**Step 1 — Create `.claude/commands/` structure** (if not present):
Verify all agent skill files exist. List any missing files.

**Step 2 — Create `.agent/` structure**:
```bash
mkdir -p .agent/status .agent/messages .agent/backlog .agent/reports
```

**Step 3 — Create status files** (for each agent that doesn't have one):
```bash
for agent in manager scrum po staff-engineer backend architect qa devops security networking documentation researcher release-manager marketing perf sre tpm; do
  [ -f ".agent/status/${agent}.md" ] || echo "---\nagent: ${agent}\nstatus: Idle\n---" > ".agent/status/${agent}.md"
  [ -f ".agent/messages/${agent}.md" ] || echo "---\n---" > ".agent/messages/${agent}.md"
done
```

**Step 4 — Create backlog** (if not present):
```bash
[ -f ".agent/backlog/tasks.md" ] || cat > .agent/backlog/tasks.md << 'EOF'
# {{projectName}} — Task Backlog

## Backlog

## In Progress

## Done
EOF
```

**Step 5 — Create `docs/` structure**:
```bash
mkdir -p docs/wiki docs/adr docs/runbooks
```

**Step 6 — Report what was created**:
List every file and directory created. Confirm the structure is complete.

**Step 7 — Write a welcome message to Manager**:
Write to `.agent/messages/manager.md`:
```
## Agent team bootstrapped (from Setup, <date>)

The .agent/ infrastructure has been created or repaired. All status and message files are initialized.

Next step: CEO should brief the team via /manager.
```

## What NOT to Do

- Do not overwrite existing status or message files (they may contain important state)
- Do not modify `.claude/commands/` files (skill definitions are the source of truth)
- Do not create content in `docs/` beyond the directory structure (Documentation owns that)
